                    <span>One Of The Best & Most Comprehensive 
<br />
<br />It's written right there on the front of the book - Understanding the Sport and Skills of Boxing - and it delivers all that and more.
<br />
<br />This is really a great book for the person interested in boxing either as a sport, an art or fitness training. It's for the novice and the ring veteran.
<br />
<br />The Ultimate Boxer is divided into 8 incredibly comprehensive chapters:
<br />Fundamentals
<br />Conditioning
<br />Science
<br />Strategy
<br />Competition
<br />Social aspects
<br />Coaching
<br />Supportive material
<br />
<br />Each chapter is complete, informative and educational. 
<br />
<br />The tips, suggestions and advice are plentiful. There's a great section on how to compete against specific styles - i.e. how to box a croucher, a southpaw, a slugger etc - as well as excellent guidance for fundamentals, conditioning and training exercises
<br />
<br />I plan to keep this by my training equipment as a reference guide and use and review over and over again.
<br /></span>
                  
